
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 06 of Elbow MRI

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Epicondylitis' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Lateral epicondylitis' radio button is enabled
And 'Medial epicondylitis' radio button is enabled

And 'Focal bone marrow edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bony erosion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Enthesiophytes' checkbox is enabled
And 'Peritendinous edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vascularization' checkbox is enabled
And 'Articular effusion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bursitis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis sign' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Lateral epicondylitis' radio button
Then 'Lateral joint capsule thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Enthesiopathy deep extensor tendons' checkbox is enabled
And 'Rupture of deep extensor tendons' checkbox is enabled

And 'Thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Rupture' checkbox is enabled

And 'Thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Rupture' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Enthesiopathy deep extensor tendons' checkbox
Then 'T2w hyperintensity' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Restricted to tendon of extensor carpi radialis brevis muscle' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Rupture of deep extensor tendons' checkbox
Then 'Partial tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Complete tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Restricted to tendon of extensor carpi radialis brevis muscle' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Complete tear' radio button
Then 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled
